Talking in sleep
Some children talk at night
I do not mean those who wake up and tell us something that happened the day before, but the children who talk during sleep.
When it happens to you for the first time, at best, you will be frightened, but in reality it has no meaning.
This is a positive sleep disorder called speaking in sleep.
It is quite common, especially among children and young people.
Surely, more than one of you has been told that you have spoken at night.
This phenomenon can occur occasionally (once in life, for example, during high fever), or regularly (every day, once a week, once a month), the next day the child can remember nothing.
There is no single reason that causes this phenomenon.
Often, associations are sought with other phenomena in sleep, such as nightmares, panic anxiety at night, enuresis noctura (bedwetting at night), speaking in sleep, but there is no reason for this.
As we have mentioned before, it can be due to very high fiber, stressful situations or overloading.
In any case, this is a little researched phenomenon.
The frequency with which it occurs is very variable.
It may be that one speaks quietly in individual words, whispers or it may be quite the opposite (screaming, crying, long discussions ).
In cases where the expression is very intense, it is recommended to observe the child and seek advice from a specialist to check whether there is a problem that causes anxiety and in this way comes about.
We have said that it is a positive disorder, so it is not treated, be it, it is associated with another sleep disorder that can be treated (for example, with sleep apnea or with stress).
What you can do is to perform a series of simple preventive measures:
Try not to excite the child before sleep.
So, choose quiet game for the child and avoid stressful TV programs that are terrible and a little too wild.
In the nervous children who are recommended to relax, relaxation methods can be used to help them get a certain inner peace.
This will help the child to sleep well.
If speaking occurs in sleep, try to keep calm.
Remember that it is harmless to the child and the next day he will not be able to remember anything that happened.
Useful advice
Don't wake it up.
This is useless, because the child is unconscious, so you will tear him out of his sleep.
Although the child speaks, he sleeps, so he rests.
Remember, if it appears frightened after a couple of appearances, it is recommended to seek advice or find out what reason the child has for the fear.
When they understand what it says (which is not so common), the child does not put pressure to conduct an interrogation and get more information out.
So you will not be able to achieve anything with it, because when the child sleeps, it is unconscious and cannot think about it.
Besides, you will hear what it says, but you will not know what it dreams and why it says it, so be careful with the interpretation of the information and the conclusions you draw from it.
Perhaps, it does not tell the child that you hear this at night and know its secrets.
Not even as a joke.
This causes a lot of fear.
So, don’t worry, it’s nothing bad, it’s a moment that only takes a few minutes.
