Plan North will be ‘discussed, regulated and environmentally friendly’, he promised.
Jean Charest described this ‘vision’ as if it were a continuation of those of the liberal prime ministers who had been in office before him.
“Like the liberals who were in office before us, we rethought to turn the challenges into new opportunities for growth and development.
