In the direction of skeptics, who are plagued by Orwellian horror visions, he says: These would just overlook the essentials of Web 2.0.
In a recent interview with the Financial Times, Schmidt said Google’s main goal was to collect even more personal data about users, bringing it closer to the company’s original goal of “ordering all the information in the world.”
