The elite is in danger.
The phenomenon had already revealed itself a few days ago, when the House of Representatives voted against the $700 billion savings package of the White House: A large part of Americans were and are more interested in punishing Wall Street than saving the economy.
This is confirmed by yesterday’s edition of the New York Times, which reports how the crisis is gradually dividing the Republican Party, which is increasingly splitting into its old and moderate East Coast soul, which has always favoured state institutions and the business community, and those neoconservatives who are hostile to “those in Washington” and the financial world and win voters, especially in the south and the center of the states.
